Q8D. Description: An event happened last year in 2021 at Chamuhula village at the municipality from Church of Christ Church. I moved home by home, telling people to be saved and preaching the gospel to people on the new religion around. But others were saved while other home members never had time to listen on the gospel. I was chased in one house like a thief encouraging to renew their faith. The theme of the preaching was got from the book of John 8:32 “You should know the truth, and the truth will set you free”, whereby 1 member to me, that “is the church buying for us food of feeding us since we were born” then told me move slowly before they will chase me. Feelings: He was so bad and not good. For me, preaching the word of the Lord is not very easy. Some homes were hostile about the new religion, “religion conflicts“

Q1. Describe Leadership Roles: School: Headboy: Oguti Primary School 2014-2015 in Tororo Municipality and I had good leadership
Q8C. Other event: Debate at school was the most event I will never forget in my life
Q8D. Description: The debate was held at Oguti Primary in 2014 in the afternoon after having lunch at 2:00-3:30 pm. The motion was “food was better than money”. Whereby the opposers and the propers attended and participated fully, and I personally was speaker of the debate. The funny thing is, we had students who really knew English well and the participation user full of laughter, joy and happiness where a pupil broke English saying “food cannot better money”, whereby every pupils and teachers were seriously having tears of joy of crying when the pupil broke the language. Therefore the opposers warn the motion “debate” and left the proposers unhappy and said they cheated by the secretary. One pupil was very annoyed and stoned the chairperson then eventually was rushed to the hospital when bleeding just because of debating. This boy who caused the incident was expelled at school. In conclusion, I felt unhappy and it's making me remember up to date about the event that happened at school.

Q1. Describe Leadership Roles: Chairman pulpit committee at Rock baptist church. handling problems taht arise within the church, counselling and problem solving. Conflict resolution.
Q8D. Description: During the Easter of 2012, there was a scenario in the church where the pastor was dragged from the pulpit never to continue preaching by a group of youth whom he had groomed. Because Pastor was not educated, foreign donations were mismanaged, a pastors was a liar, etc. There was physically fighting in the course of removing the pastor, so the youth took over the church and another pastor was appointed who worked for two years. Another group within the church removed him due to allegations of embezzlement of church funds. The group that removed the pastor had their interests and now the mother-in-law is of women leader or treasurer, the wife is the choir leader/children's groups, brother-in-law is the youth leader. Having seen that, I resigned and got a second thought about the church. The impact in my life is that what happens in church is not for spiritual purposes. This made me change my religion back to the Catholic Church.

Q8D. Description: In the year 2001, I stopped going to church, even though that is what I consider as my in-group. I used to be caned at school, at home and even at church. I hated school and eventually hated church too. Since then being caned at church affected my life negatively and I have never been at church for close to 21 years now. I hope to begin going to church again. I also felt so sad when I was forced to separate with my wife due to tribal conflicts and it's impacted me negatively since we had three children together, it has been three years of sadness.

Q8D. Description: Early this year, we lost our cultural leader ithe “Emorimor”. The event really had a significant impact on my life. It brought people together from various walks of life. The Japs and the Itesots came together. It was then that the king of the Badama said that we need to bury or differences. That the Itesots should be free to marry the Japadhola and vice versa. The party joined us together, we cut the cake, differences were put aside and I was really happy.

Q8D. Description: At the moment when I first held my grandchild in the year 2000.The commonly known as the Millennium period. My daughter gave birth to a baby girl and I saw myself growing in her as well as my generation continuing because she is married as well. In life there are several factors rather things that factor in maturity and development or growth. To me, therefore, when I saw my first grandchild, I had to regard myself as a mature person, for I had longed to also at one time carry a grandchild which in real sense means continuity in life through the newborn child. Generations are renewed through our offsprings and therefore if you produce a child who fails to give birth to any child, it means your family lineage is gone. There is no way you can resurrect through any other person, therefore me who has got such a chance of carrying a grand child feels great.

Q8D. Description: It was in 1991 when I converted from Protestant church to Islam, and one day in 2001 as I went to the mosque for prayers, our day of the day told the congregation that anyone who is handling alcohol was and will be cursed, yet my business at that time was buying and selling alcohol. On receiving that message, I immediately stopped buying and selling alcohol and opted for the business of loading and offloading salt to other parts of the community whose demand for salt was high and I later realized that the salt business was more profitable than the alcohol business. And besides, I was also able to employ some of the community members in my salt business.

Q8D. Description: In the year 2002 there was a savings group which had considered only the widows old women. I wished to join, but it seemed so restricted. At one time in 2010, I asked for permission to join them and ask and interact with them, they welcomed me. I suggested the idea of living it to be open whoever wished to join and they seconded the idea, many people join. The savings group as grown and now we get short term loans with low interest. At the end of the year we share our dividends and women have learned to save and benefit by paying school fees for their children, do small business, and we do interact with each other when we meet.

Q8D. Description: It was in the year 2009 when I married my wife. All my life I have been an orphan so I worked so hard to get families with people so as to be converted. Because of being an orphan, I always had no one to turn to so when clocked the age of 22 years, I saw it wife to marry. Ever since I got married, my life began having meaningful turnover. I automatically began to gain respect from people and not pity. Everyone begin looking at me as a responsible man and a true man. Seeing that I had gained weight among the people, and especially having become a father as well, I came.Out to campaign for a position of being a general secretary. Little did I know that.Once was on my side. Everyone was talking good about me and about myself or my and my family at large. I want my opponents by a very large number of votes. I am sure that it is because I succeeded in marrying a Good Wife that I am able to be a great man that I am currently because before I got married I had tried but was all in vain. I am now a Defense Secretary of the whole parish and I am hopeful that I will go councillor and also MP as well.

I and my friends planned to go and enjoy ourselves.The two of them used a motorcycle and I boarded a taxi.They were ahead of me because the motorcycle moved faster than public means. Q8D. Description: Becoming a defense leader on the LCI committee and.Over the whole of my village, before I gained that position, I was merely a peasant farmer who always cooked out for others, but only in my family or clan and a few friends. While at home I was a security on volunteer basis of the family. I never knew people could trust me with such responsibility of the law. We were 11 people eyeing to that position, but out of them all I emerged the best. I am hopeful that I will in future be a counselor because I know for sure that being good to others surely can earn you leadership and I am making connections towards that.

Q8D. Description: The baptism of my first born child who is a girl. This happened on 16/7/2012 when we officially went to church and baptized her. It was on this very day something special happened to me because that is when my husband convinced in Church that he is going to introduce me and pay dowry to my parents home by the end of the year. My baby (our baby) received a lot of gifts like clothes, baby toys, oil/baby jellies. We received so many visitors at home somethings that had never happened to me ever since I got married 2010. That moment of baprizing our baby was so cool is since so special to me in my life.

Q8D. Description: Being arrested due to a rumor that I had a gun at my home in June 1987. A whole full of army ambushed me from home, got me arrested and I was taken to Rubongi Baracks. I was in so much fear, shock and panic thinking my life had ended. I lost a lot of hope asking myself, even though I am a Defense Secretary, could not they understand that I am naturally a law abiding citizen.This all happened during NRM regime. However, I got to even understand power.And.Leadership the more as they parish chief and subcounty chief of Nagongera console a letter to the barracks insuring them that I have no such item in my possession. They investigated and researched my home over and over several times, but around a period of one week after arrest, I was released and set free. I even became much more popular to the extent that I managed to get that position at the sub county, a lot of people got to know me and later on was even voted the chairman LCI of Awanyi village now for 21 years since 2001.

Q8D. Description: Last year my friend Salim had a wedding ceremony. I myself participated in the preparation and we went with fifteen people. We were welcomed warmly by the new-in-laws. After we sat down in the shelter which had been built for us. Everybody came and greeted us. Thereafter the father-in-law and the mother-in-law came last. After greetings were exchanged, the bride came into the shelter escorted by several girls. She the introduced Salim to her relatives. How Salim now presented the gifts we had brought to his in-laws. Being Muslims, the next day Salim wife Zainabu had to go to the mosque for the self introduction. The event of Moslem wedding was challenging to me and I will not forget of the ceremony.

Q8D. Description: The day I celebrated my birthday. It was on 10/01/2005 when my parents surprised me with a birthday party. I used to hear about birthdays, but I had never celebrated one as a person. Actually, all my friends at school had never celebrated it. We used to tell ourselves that such parties are for the rich families. Ever this happening totally changed my perspective about that because I celebrated my birthday even though I came from a poor home. This made me to double my effort in studies at school so as to please.Them by excelling in academics, I improved, but due to sickness I had I could not go yet because I could convulse all the time while at school. I will live to always remember that moment.

Q8D. Description: I vividly remember the incident of my mother's death in 1989.Yet I was away in exile. Wasn't able to bury my mother, who died under unclear circumstances, but what my siblings told me is that her word was if “I were around, she wouldn't have died.” What pains me most is that this is because of my cows she was keeping that people used witchcraft to kill her and enable them to steal the animals in peace.After Mom's death I realized I needed to work, but also not so distant from home, because since then I had to take over responsibilities at home and also take care of my little siblings then.Revive our land that had become bushy. I returned and had to restart connecting with our people. I changed my life from that of being. A safari man to tending with the community I am well raised and conversant with.

Q8D. Description: I was employed in Kampala and I felt I needed to improve the life of my siblings. So I decided to invite my brothers to stay with me as I looked out for opportunities for him to start earning. But instead my brother decided to make my wife his spouse in the year 2000. I one time found them having sex on my bed. Since that day I decided to leave Kampala and even left my wife for him. They even have three children now. However, one thing I have failed to overcome now is drunkenness. I started drinking alcohol that day and I no longer understand my life, but I will finally, let go. I ended up in a new marriage with a spouse with whom we don't share ethnicity.

Q8D. Description: In 2019 I traveled to Saudi Arabia to work as a house help. So on this fateful morning in 2020, I got a bad accident. I hit my head on the ceiling as I woke up from my uppermost bed then got convulsions, migraine headaches and constant nose bleeding for close to a year. But this particular day in 2021, I decided to turn to God as a desperate and lost solution and indeed, I felt a lot better. Remember, I was in a Muslim setting, but I had to secretly say my prayers in tears, in my own room and quietly until I had an encounter with God. I will not forget that day. A weight was lifted off my life. I got instant recovery and even my employers wondered how that happened. Kept telling myself whom is better, you can at least face death among your people, and one can pray freely without hiding. Since then I find power in freedom of religion.For me, the moment I got healed from that condition is very OK to me, because then I believe thath there's invisible power and authority when you believe in God.

Q8D. Description: It was the year 2015, after I already had five children, when I decided to convert from Church of Uganda to Pentecostal assembly which my husband then was against. So he decided to divorce me to the extent that he sharpened a panga for me to leave his home and immediately moved in with another woman. I will never forget how he celebrated my acceptance to leave his home by doing a goat roast. This whole divorce thing has had a bad impact in my life. My children got scattered and I lost touch with them and the result is I am now squatter in a person’s home and subjected to doing donkey garden work. I lost touch with everyone except my last born, who I left with at her crawling stage. I have never believed that marriage can work out when you have a different beliefs especially for us who are not so educated.

Q8D. Description: The year 2013 was a horrible year. My own husband forced me.To abort seven months pregnancy with a claim of being financially incapacitated, yet in actual sense he only wanted to enjoy his life. We had a heated argument with him and a doctor, to the point that my own husband denied having conjugal obligations with me. I painful give in to that abortion and my life was in danger. He decided to abandon me until I recovered. I will never forget this day because not even a single friend was there for me. I was on my own. However, I know and believe that it was divine power that I am still alive. I keep asking God to rest his mercy upon me and my husband for because we did.Offer God humanly.No one has a right to take a life, but I'm grateful to God that I am a lot stronger than I used to be. I can feel for my family and I advocate for pro-life.But again, I keep asking myself where my church friends the times they knew I was having a violent marriage? I learnt not to trust people except God.

Q8D. Description: It was in 2016 when I stood surity for a friend of mine to get an SME loan from a money kender on receiving the money from the lender my friend disappeared with the money without aying back any installment of the money. As a surity, I was arrested and taken to prison. This affected my life and the community members because even the savings group collapsed due to my absence. After suspending 21 days in prison, the actual person who took the money was arrested and I was released from prison. This brought joy to my family and the community members and we were able to begin our savings group with even more members joining us.

Q8D. Description: It was in 2006 during my wedding and because of the historical clashes between the two main tribes in Tororo the Itesot and the Jap. I and my husband were all scared because it was an intertribal marriage. For sure, I cannot forget that day.

Q8D. Description: Visiting relatives.I have been CaringBridge relatives. It was in 1972 when I was 24 years. I decided to go and visit my uncle in Tororo cement industry. I eventually ended staying there as one of the children in his home. My uncle took me up, got me a driving permit and connected me to the factory as a driver. There, my life surely started turning around for good, because I even joined other companies as driver of quality animal feeds in Kampala. I really started making money. I was able to get married, have children and educated all my children without struggling. I also managed to construct my own home and I am now a stable man, up to date because of what my uncle did to me. Besides, I have also helped so countless number of people to join the transport sector as well as employing three other driver for myself, they drive my own cars.

Q8D. Description: That optimism of my child, the second it was during 2019, during the COVID-19 period, when churches had just been opened. I went to our Catholic Church, Saint Paul, to baptize my child. As usual, I thought I would become with other few relative, because my husband had assured me that he would be around for the ceremony. However, to my surprise, when the Rev Father stepped in, I was in the line when I turned back behind me. To my surprise, I saw my husband be and guess he had come in, particularly to see me baptize our child together.I was totally saved of the embarrassment of being at the altar alone without the baby's father. That was the most important and colorful event in my life. It has made me surely get very strengthened in my marriage.

Q8D. Description: The time when our school football team won a trophy to the whole school. I studied from LCCI primary school and in the year 1990 I was among the school team football players. We played against six schools and emerged the best. By then I was in primary 5 class. I was teh shortest in that class though as you can see me now, I am not the shortest person. Not much was expected from me in regards to scoring the goals. Actually at one point they even wanted to replace during the second-half. But my coach insisted that I keep in because I am an active person. Surprisingly, I scored in the 5 minutes. There was a celebration because it was a winning goal. Since then sometimes people call me footballer and I have always played even here in the village with fellow peers. People call me coach because of what happened on that day.

Q8D. Description: Wedding event. It was Saturday 12/5/2013, My Real wedding celebration that was celebrated at Mahanga Catholic. As on the way to the church we were celebrating. Christians were singing along the road. Very happy escorting.T to church. And the prayer was led by the parish priest. After the prayers in church, the celebration was extended at home at 11:30 AM, many people were invited. Even the different cultural leaders were present. Thereafter when reaching home the home had changed because of the decoration. Music was sounding so high that it was my first time music to be played at my home. Whereby I felt so happy, joyful and pleased, I received many gifts that accept that excepted and I won my husband on gifts and money, cows, goats. That event changed my life and my husband a lot that showed respect and the Community that I was wedded. The event makes me remember up to date.

Whereby I felt so happy, joyful and pleased, I received many gifts that accept that excepted and I won my husband on gifts and money, cows, goats. That event changed my life and my husband a lot that showed respect and the Community that I was wedded. The event makes me remember up to date.

Q8D. Description: Saving group member this has treated me very well much as I like a poor woman from an impoverished household I am able to get the basic needs, especially be able to celebrate Christmas with a lot of joy. I joined a savings group in 2000. We are 30 Members and I have managed to be there until now. Back then, even on Christmas Day, we could sometimes eat greens or lack food and only receive food from those who would sympathize with us. On a daily basis, life was always hard as I used to always have quarrels with my husband's domestic violence because my husband cannot provide at all because he likes drinking. Then my friends and neighbors advice I at least join a savings group, which I did, and I have lived to see so many changes. Domestic violence stopped and now I am also supporting my family with basic needs. In December when we share the money I can also buy good clothes for us and meat even food thus no begging from others.

Q8D. Description: In the past few years, actually the last two years, my last born passed on through an accident from Alaba.He left his wife and two grandchildren, whom I took over to care of them. The incident was very sad. It left me so devastated, wondering of what to do at this old age of mine. However, I got very surprised. The area councillor on the LC, I took over the child to pay for school fees. The family members came in to support. I can see everyone is very empathetic and supportive.I have not suffered like I thought because.The clan has eventually united and everyone is supportive of us, including the politicians.I am thankful to the Lord that he has done me this great favor. My husband is so old now 110 years, but he is also not stressed by that. We are both thankful.

I was so devastated, the being both a widow and a single mother as well.At first Life was really unbearable, but later on things begin to get better because the government, through the sub county, began to help the widows and orphaned children.The community gave in my name and I am now being helped.However, my relatives have come in so much to help me, even those that I never knew. Surely everyone lives so hard to make sure that I don't lack or feel lonely.Actually, when my husband was still alive, I seemed to see that I even suffered more because now people give.Me food, they.Help to educate my grandchildren. I thank God that he has helped me.

Q8D. Description: I will never forget the day I went for say sorry again for my second born. In 2010, my baby was lying in a broach position that time of delivery. The midwives were so rude and difficult to deal with. However, the most pathetic bit is that everything happened when I had already lost consciousness. It was terrible labor scenario. It was only with friends and inlaws due to the fact that my own relatives live quite far from here.To me.It brought France closer, even those that sought divine intervention, for me to have a safe operation had to first bury their differences to ensure that they at least stand with me. This event /birth of my baby keeps ringing a bell that even when we differ in beliefs and ways of practicing faith, a matter of life or death can actually cause unity and a better forms of communication. A very thin line between life and death.

Q8D. Description: In 2015, some missionaries that we were working with started many churches together with us after taking us to Bible tracing. I was reading about 48 churches. The missionaries were happy with our work and wanted to sponsor us. He got the spouses but said later on that she did not need us and the lead missionary chased us out of the ministry. We came back to the village and began suffering. I had left my job as advisor for ministry. This event hurt me so much and my friends, 10 in total. It was challenging. My children could not go to school. Feeling was a challenge and I was so heartbroken and I really struggled with life. The conflicts in church really pained me, but I have now joined a new ministry.

Q8D. Description: In 2020 we lost one of our friends in the group, Boda Boda stage. We collected money that was too much, but it was sufficient enough to organize for the burial. He died because of a motorcycle accident. The group acted as a single unit and all the other Boda bodas admired our group. I was so touched by the group solidarity and the village member said that it was one of the best burials. From that day I was appointed as a leader for the stage and I felt like we are one. I am not alone. I am not afraid if anything happens to me because I know that I have friends to stand by me. The stage (Boda Boda) has a mixture of all ethnicities and religions.

Jesus is the only solution to this tribal conflicts in Tororo.

I believed my children would not grow because I wasn't able to take care of them.The pastor counseled me, prayed for me and told me never to think about it again. He started for me a small business where it now happened to raise school fees for my children. Right now I have a teacher for secondary and a lawyer, and my daughter is about to finish her nursing course.

Q8D. Description: In 2008, I was renting, then the landlord to me. I'm going on the roof, the build, you can transfer somewhere. While there I worked hard and started constructing my house slowly and now I am at my home. The situation made me think big and now achieved a home.

Q8D. Description: In the year 2006. I was staying with mother who gave birth to me at their home. She told me to come to my father's home in Tororo, where I had never stayed. At that time I was 12 years old. I reached my father's home and they chased me that. My mother should show me the father because at their home a child is shown where they belong while still and not at my age. After a week, my father gave me a small room to stay but told me he cannot pay my school fees.I had to struggle for myself and raise some fees until I finished P7. After this level I could not afford and started to cultivate rice, maize, groundnuts. I bought my hand, goats and a cow.I later married my wife out of the struggle and I was able to pay my own dowry to her parents.

Q8D. Description: It was family meeting. I came back home to attend and it was on Saturday last year when my father called us, all the children for a meeting. I was given a share at home, such as a plot of land in case my marriage fail in future. Then another thing I was given was 1 cow and then gave me one door at the trading center. Meeting my dad called US home, has made my life live as a good testimony that having parents is a good aspect in life.There for that day went on well and I can never forget about the meeting.

Q8D. Description: In the year 2000, my husband decided to abandon me with our six children in the village and he married another woman in town and never could he even come back. I suffered a lot selling small foods at a primary school to take care of the children. One day a friend of mine told me to follow her to church after seeing the way I was talking and suffering as a single mother. He then accepted and went with her and the pastor located me that my husband had been bewitched by his stepmother who never wanted us to prosper at all. We continue in prayer in same church as a pastor still helped one of my sons to get a sponsor who now pay his school fees. After a long time in church, I was surprised to see my husband back by himself and come very excited until now we are together again.

He rarely comes home, so things turned out to be very difficult for me in terms of providing household items.Food.However, with the counseling of my aunt, I managed to join a group of women who help each other in the gardens. My aunt also connected me to some teacher and I have been offered a job as a cook at a nearby school. I'm able to feed my children and also help myself.

Q8D. Description: I used to be a drunked and I could waste a lot of money in buying alcohol.However, in 2021 there was a church sermon by the priest and he touched me. I ended up giving up on alcohol. I stopped going to the bar and I refused to respond to calls from people who wanted me to go to drink.When I stopped the habit of drinking, I was able to save much money up to close to 34M shs. I was able to use The money to build a house for myself and also build good working network with the others in the land broker business. This leaving alcohol has really made me to be very exemplary in my community and also be happy with my family members.

It pained me a lot because the family income is little. I even decided to go back to my father's home.In 2021, I came back home to keep my children. I started going for daily prayers at church and I also got involved in the novena prayers.The chairperson of the women guilt took interest in me. They visited me as a team and encouraged me to keep my home. Currently I am at peace and have forgiven my husband. The other woman does not stay with me in my compound. They rent for her other trading center. I am happy to be at my home.

Q8D. Description: I grew up in a very humble background, my father could not afford taking me to school. In 1959, my brother decided to take me to school through education. Q8D. Description: I was married, but my husband changed his character and become abusive. I divorced him in 2000 and decided to live at my father's home. However, things were still difficult as my sisters-in-law used to quarrel with me a lot, even over minor things. I worked hard by digging and selling silver fish. In 2005, I was able to get my own money and I bought a plot of land in this village. I also constructed a house where I am living in right now. At church, the priest teaches us how to forgive those who wrong you. I forgive my relatives and now we are happy. They consult with me on issues that affect our home. Everything is moving on well.

As a leader, I encourage youth and elders it's good to work with people together. Sharing things and God will provide you many things. The event that occurred that date, I will never forget it in my life.

They ordered me to bring out all the money I had. Led me to the crate and took my cows carried my clothes and beddings and left us at zero. Without anything in the village I hustled with my family and almost lacked what to eat. It was my neighbor that helped me for some time, but also reached a time and gave up. I thank God I have a hard working woman who helped me and we got back to normal.

Q8D. Description: When I got pregnant the first time. It was a big challenge because my boyfriend abandoned me. After giving birth, I had to look for the job with the primary goal of looking after my child because I had now grown as an adult and cannot keep on depending on parents. I got a job in somebody's shop as a shopkeeper and since then that marked a twist of my life because I could barely be in charge of everything. Looking after the child, my parents and also had to be responsible for my own life actions. I grew up more than expected and have been responsible until now, even when I am married.

Q1. Describe Leadership Roles: Taking care of my parents and siblings
Q8D. Description: The life of being from a very poor and impoverished household, pushed to make sure I step up or out to support my parents and siblings at a very young age of 16 years old. The inability of my parents to sustain me in school really challenged me. I started working by selling scrap and also trying out other business ventures like raising poultry so as to educate my siblings as well as support my parents by buying food at home pay for hospital bills etc. So far I have managed to educate my siblings whereby one is senior four and the other is senior 6. I have also managed to make my own business and I feel that I am out of the impoverished lifestyle. I at least have my own hardware shop and have constructed for my parents. If my parents never fail to provide for us back then i would not have turned out to be the person i am .

Q8D. Description: In 2017, I had planted sugar cane with my neighbor. Our gardens were adjacent with one another. Unfortunately, one day there was a fire outbreak and both our sugar cane were burnt.He's burnt down completely while mine had at least a few remaining. He then accused me of carrying out the act. I was reported to police. I didn't sleep in the cells, but we were in and out of court for three consecutive years. Finally I was made to pay him a fine of 3,000,000. Since then have come home to realize that not everyone who rubbed shoulders with is a friend, but also my conclusion of this is because we come from different ethnic background that's why we failed to resolve this amongst ourselves.

Q8D. Description: My son, the son to my brother, bought me land just as a gift in 2008 and it is the only gift that I have ever received in my life. Having grown up without receiving any kind of gift from anyone in life, this came at a time when it was long-awaited. This gift did not only bring joy to me, but to the whole family, since the very piece of land was used to cultivation and thus a source of food to the family.And this implied a source of income to the family brought peace in the family, above all promoting unity in the family.I therefore regard 2008 as one of my unique years as down with all of happiness in my family, for the lease for the land promoted unity among my family and several interests of people.

Q8D. Description: The day of my wedding in 2001 September. When I was 17 years old and my wife 56 years, that is something that I had almost given up in life. Q8D. Description: Compensation from Civil Aviation Authority, where I was given 11 million, the money which had helped me to start up my business in the year 2016. The business I let up is produced and selling music system. Quiet, challenging for a civil servant to serve money while still working, but when I received the compensation I really saw a great opportunity that would help me develop myself and transform my life. Compensation money which helped me to start up a business has enhance the family standard of living and also brought services nearer to the community. The very business.Acts as a meeting point for community members and in the long run, we end up mixing freely as members of the same group rather community. Me and my family are living a happy life and joyfully moments which came as a result of the compensation.

Q8D. Description: Six years ago, my wife went and left me with our three children because of baseless rumors. I had uh radio that people in the community would hire for their occasions and I would stay with them overnight and on my return she would accuse me of being with other women. She went on with this for some time, however much I explained to her, eventually she left for good. I have not had it easy raising these children. It has really been hard. It cost me a lot of conflicts with even my neighbors.

She wanted me dead when I was six months pregnant, she cost me birth pains which almost took my life. I had to leave the marriage and since then my husband has not taken care of us at all. I struggle alone. I try my best and sometimes my aunt helps me.

Q8D. Description: In 2020 I lived in an area called Area 40 Agururu B1 where I had a nasty experience with neighbors concerning children. The children would fight and the parents of the others would want to fight back. These neighbors made my life unbearable. I could not even leave any of my property at my door. They could look for any slight reason to provoke me and cause a quarrel with me. I could not bear it, so I had to come to Agururu A to rent where my mental health is stable.

Q8D. Description: My husband died in 2019. Our cows had been stolen and my mother-in-law did some witchcraft which backfired on the son. The witchcraft killed my husband and after his death his people tempted to evict me from the house.It took the LCI chairman and his voice to stop them. Since we are Muslims, these two leaders took the case to the Imam who ruled in our favor. It took Me 2 years to stabilize from the emotional trauma. Till now I am still just picking up pieces here and there for the sake of my very young children.The second is just three years. If it was not for my parents, who have supported me emotional and financially, I don't know what I would do. My in-laws wanted me to leave the house and remarried since I'm still young.

Q8D. Description: In 2019 I went abroad thinking things were hard in Uganda. I went to work in the Arab Emirates for two years, as the contract had indicated. But I got to know that life that side was not good at all. At one point I become suicidal because I couldn't take in the mistreatment and the load of work with very less sleep. My family were very worried back home.T hey thought I would not make it back home alive, but with prayers and the grace of God, I managed to finish the two years, but with poor health. It's a mistake I will not make again.

Q8D. Description: After my senior year four, as my parents was preparing to take me to school, I made a mistake and got pregnant for a man who turned my life upside down. After all, a mistake I would not want my children to get through, not even at one point.After a few years, he began dating several women to the extent of him selling household items so as to take care of the women.He frustrated me beyond until I was pushed to do something I still cannot believe I would ever do because I was a born again Christian. I bewitched his manhood in that when he is other woman, his manhood cannot function normally.He doesn't erect. I backslide. I don't think I can go to a Pentecostal church again. I now pray from an Anglican church he's going to be like that until he changes his ways.

Q8D. Description: I was tortured by my stepmother, especially in 2019. I was 20 years when I and my siblings began staying with our stepmother in Kampala. She denied I and my siblings.Food and other basic needs. She often would lock me out.I even failed to finish my cosmetology course because of her. At one point I was forced to sleep with an older man so that I can take care of my siblings.Along the way I got pregnant, but I could not come to term with it because it's not what I wanted and there was no way I was going to give birth to a curse and hated baby, so I gladly aborted the pregnancy.I so much blame my father for making me go down a path I was not supposed to go through. He didn't stand for us right now. I'm expected, but I wouldn't be married at this age. I had big dreams as a girl. All that has been shattered. I am so bitter. But I have to let go.

Q8D. Description: The prgenancy. I got pregnant but this was all just a mess whereby I was in a relationship which was not that serious because it was all about having a boyfriend and not for marriage. We ended up messing up and as of me especially I even had to drop out school at a level of senior four class and now I am staying at my parent’s place. My whole life has changed but for the better because right now even at home all people including my parents just underlook. No one takes me serious apart from my mother. Actually currently I feel very bad about the pregnancy because already I am economically incapacitated though I have already grown to being an adult. However, in the midstof all these feelings I am sure about one thing that I will never make such a mistake and especially if I get a chance to go back to school I will study and complete without ever wasting any money at school. I have learnt to make life seriously and all the opportunities taht come around because I have matured though hardships. I am a changed girl for the better.

Q8D. Description: My husband is amudaama and am an Itesot from Busia. When I met my husband in one of the market days in Busia things connected and we agreed to settle as a family. When I was introduced to the family, it was only my husband who was happy that day the rest of the members were showing hate. Actually the family has never liked me, I remember everything that I have faced in my marriage. In fact if it wasn’t for my husband I wouldn't have left long time. The rift between Itesot and Amudaama in Tororo needs just God intervention cause I didn’t expect this people to hate me even knowing I have their children.

Q8D. Description: Annual Youth Seminar/Camp at Church. Business enterprise coaching. Spiritual renewal. Youth connections. Hands on skills like baking, craftship. The business enterprise coaching impacted on the community cause most ladies got equipped with skills to start their own business and own their assets like land big capitals. Q8D. Description: The ability to pay dowry for my wife on 24/10/2008. On that day i was officially married and called a real man. We started our relationship in a very impoverished lifestyle, very poor, with almost nothing to sleep on. Everyone thought that my wife will after all leave me, that marriage over marriage wont last for long. However, those words all never came to pass. I paid dowry in 2008 and we are still together up to now 16 years of marriage. So many people turned up for our introduction. In our village here, people do all regard us as people who are capable of doing developmental things in life and also feel underprivileged. But all in all I thank God for I managed to pay fees, a thing which left my in-laws happy and my family too.

Also, other members who wanted to wed were able to learn that a church members can support you. Besides, it has strengthened my relationship with Christ since I now believe that with God everything is possible.

Q8D. Description: In 2008, two of my brothers had a conflict over a lady that they wanted to marry. The conflict was so sore that as a clan chairman I had to call for a meeting. The brothers had fought an even injured each other. To prevent death, we had to solve the problem by having a clan meeting. I would be left alone by now if my brothers had killed each other. Being the chairman and reconciling my brothers is the most important thing in my life and most important event in my clan. I will always remember it. On top of that day i married was good, i married a japadhola but their men are terrible and i hate the Japadhola men on the contrary their women are okay. The japadolla as jealousy of the Iteso men .

Q8D. Description: When I was five years old, I lost my mother and I was only the second born at the time. Our father tried to take care of us, but he could not do much. At the age of eight, my sister got me a job in town as a house girl. Worked till I was 16 years of age and then married. My mother had not died. I believe I would have gone for with education and not married at an early age. I was barely a child myself when I married. This event affected my siblings as well because we didn't get any support from relatives or community members. I would have been in a much better position than this.

Q8D. Description: In the year 2020 April I went to work in.Moroto but ended stock due to lockdown. There were no cars to bring us home and no work either. Our boss maneuvered and made us to use lorries that carry stones. It was an interesting moment because of the way we moved, because we had no money and had lost hope of getting back home.Our boss had got fed up of us because he was supposed to feed us for as long as we were still in his hands. Generally, life was hard as the situation got worsened. Our boss had to resort to making us use lorries that carry stones from Moroto.

Q8D. Description: The day I became a pastor in the month of November 2013. I feel I have grown and have the power to surely lead in the ministry. I am very much humbled and honestly I am very well known in very many different communities. I am always recognized on functions and by the society, something that had never happened to me before. Back then I was just a common man who would command no respect at all. I could attend community meetings, but actually my voice would almost not be heard because even if I share an opinion, no one would take it seriously. However, at the moment end because of being a leader, especially Pastor. I surely participate in Community decision making as people even do consult with me on serious Community development matters like family counseling and mentorship.

Q8D. Description: It was in the year 2000. I was the chairman of the Malwa (alcohol) group. We came up with an idea of collecting foods for buying a bull to be slaughtered during Christmas. We were able to buy 2 bulls. So precisely on the 26th of December. I was given 5 kilograms of meat as a bonus (top up) for being chairman. They also brought for me a suit during that time and everyone in the group was so happy and excited. I will never forget that Christmas and that day, all the days of my life.

Q8D. Description: In 2016, there was a scenario in Morikiswa on which mother Mary appeared in a banana plantation. It was announced over the radio and people went there to see what had happened. So I went with my parents. I was so surprised because I never believed it would happen. She was standing there for about two days in the plantation. It left a lasting impact in my life and the life of other Catholic believers. Our faith in God grew so much and I will never forget about that day.

Q8D. Description: There are seven years of my life that I will never forget, 2015-2021 when I was in prison. I was charged with rape case, which they act I still regret up to now. The life in prison is hell and if it wasn't for the counselors, I think I would have committed suicide. Christians has its own lessons in life and most people who have been in prisons are allergic to crime and criminal acts. There is no respect for humans in prisons because even suspects are treated as criminals. Am recovering from that trauma caused. My family is very supportive

Q8D. Description: The problem started when I joined P7 in 2018. You know, I was all normal and willing to study to accomplish my dream of being a teacher. But when I reached P7, I started experiencing attacks that couldn't allow me to enter class and when I entered class I can't write anything. Sometimes I just black out. Have been home for four years now. My parents have tried to pray for me. Though I'm feeling fine. I don't know whether I can be able to enter class again because the bad memories of what happened or still disturbing me. I'm just thinking of doing a hands on skills cause I believe my dreams of being a teacher have been scattered.

Q8D. Description: In 2019 when I was in Gulu, I buried my three friends (3 Brothers).They happened to be in the same bus that was destined for Kitgum and the bus lost control. They all died on spot and were buried same day, same time.This left me insane up to now. Whenever I sit, I get lost in such emotions how death can steal three people at once. However, at burial funeral, the preacher asked all those that had a grudge with the family to forgive, let go and reconcile because to him it seems it was a death of a certain pattern attached to the past disagreements of the family with other community members due to differences in tbeliefs and tradition. This particular family that lost the three was deep rooted in tradition that light.

Q8D. Description: Getting born again. In my life, before I got born again, I used to be over drink, using women and young girls here and there or oftenly wasting money and always violent. It was almost having no purpose in life, but ever since I got born again, my life has surely turned around. For example, I am married and I am a head of household. I can pay school fees to my children and I am able to tell what is good and bad in the society. In my social life I have been able to make responsible friends and have managed to save and construct my own house where I currently stay with my whole family.

Q8D. Description: Being a youth leader at parish level in my community. This was in the year 2017 when I jokingly enrolled at campaign in Soroti. I was just 21 years of age but people voted me. Actually as a young child I suffered so much brutality from friends. Village mates and worst of all being bullied while at school. That haunted me and I said to myself that I will not down and watch violence happen to other people. Even at home only daddy used to bit mummy so mucha and I did not like it. However, now I can talk bout human rights, freedome of speech where I be because I am very much empowered. People even call me councillor because I speak a lot and majority call me a voice to the voiceless. I feel I will make it in life. Leadership empowered me so much and I have connections because I also do mobilisation of community in case of any development program around in this village.

Q8D. Description: What was the 13 years old my father passed on and life took a terrible turn for us at home. Shortly after, my mom left us at home as children and went ahead and married another man. We were left to feed for ourselves. Later on, I left home and went in search for work in Mubende, where I worked as a waitress in a hotel. That is where I found my current husband, with whom I have two children.

Q1. Describe Leadership Roles: Riding a boat on lake Victoria in the area of Waka Waka (boat rider)
Q8D. Description: When I first paid school fees for my children at school back then in 1989, I never knew that I would be able to educate a child and most especially pray children to go to school and also staying in school. Knowing well that I am a single parent.I started working very hard with the extent of renting a boat to ride on Lake Victoria, do business and earn enough to keep my children in school and also have a good home. I did boat riding for three years, got money, started another business of selling fish something that greatly elevated my life for good because of boat riding I managed to get money that bought a plot of land and constructed in a house that we are currently staying in. Besides, the business of selling fish is what I am still doing up to now, but I did not let my children go to school where thety demanded school fees. You would not know the importance of working hard to get money.I would never feel the joy of having your children graduate from Makerere University. I am a happy mother, though they both currently not have jobs, but I have hope that they will get.

Q8D. Description: I was raised by a single mother who always tried to provide everything to me, but in 2013 she failed to raise from nutrition.I pray to God and from nowhere. My father had never paid my tuition from my childhood appeared and cleared my fees. I was able to finish my course and went for further studies which has made me what I am today. I am currently a parish chief and I am playing a great role in community sanctization and mobilization, leading campaigns against violence within the community, fighting for children's rights, especially for the girl child, among others.

Q8D. Description: I was a Protestant Christian who got married to a Muslim man who would later refuse me from going to any church for prayers, but wanted me to always go for prayers in a mosque against my wish. But I kept on praying to God about my condition. Fortunately, one day in 2018, I requested my husband to allow me to go to church for prayers and granted my request which turned out to become a testimony. So when I went to a born again church until is now my church to share my testimony. I Christian (brother) contributed some money for me. I use that money to start a business of buy and sell firewood which has boosted my family income and the income of people whom i buy firewood from.

Q8D. Description: The time when I was working and my aunts school as a shopkeeper and I was the overall in charge. My aunt trusted me so much. This was in 2002 when I was about 24 years old. Could not finish up school because of school fees issues. Since I am an orphan, I supported with getting what to eat. Some of my siblings went to work for other people as shamba boys. Others porters but I was a shopkeeper business of selling scrap and sometimes I burn bricks and sell them. I have also managed to feed my family members and married a wife because we now have two children together. Yes, I am still struggling, but somehow life is a bit better. The shop improved my life and I am thankful for that.

Before I was elected to be a.Lead Christian I always yearned to be in that position, but I could not see myself anywhere near that.I always worked as a town Agent, Secretary, LCI of the village, but always wished to be at the top management leadership role in church. Myself esteem was so low because I thought that role who bid in one of those that are new God, but little did I know that I am too. However, in 1998 all my life turned around for good because I could now interrest directly with priests, bishops and out of that I was made a chairperson school management committee here in Kwapa primary school. We have retired a happy man with a lot of legacy like being.And foundation body and actually St Lawrence Secondary School in 2003. Post a block with an intention of changing place.Introduce feed system for pupils in school in Kwapa Primary School. Being a head Christian made achieve all that.

Q8D. Description: Being made a family leader in 2011/02/12, a day when our only surviving parent passed on and that was our mother. Are you trying moment for us as a family I could not imagine ever to see happiness again because my mother has passed on living to be total orphans and here being made a family leader of such an impoverished household. It was all sad. I thought our family had come to an end. I just accepted the responsibility because anyway it is my family and I am the elder sister. However, in every challenge there is a tunnel of light somewhere and I am happy to see that come to us in our family. I was 20 years of age.We got immense support from the clan members and also some well wishers like neighbors, friends to the extent that I am now married have been able to pay fees for all my siblings in school. Some relatives are also helping out in paying for some other children. I can also mentor some other.Girls, even boys in our society to always be strong no matter what, and actually I am looked at as a living example by so many families.

Q8D. Description: The moment my parents accepted me to get married was.Best thing that ever happened to me. I was 22 years old and I got married in 2014.I had already dropped out of school and sat home for quite a long period of time. I was not bright in class so I kept on repeating classes.So when my boyfriend, who is currently my husband, came home to parents to ask for my hand in marriage, which I eagerly wanted, they surely consented. Back then, when I was still home with my parents, they used to abuse me, that I will get old from my parents home, no one will marry me, and that I am not beautiful enough for men to get attracted to me. Some aunties used to tell me that if I got married, I won't even give birth. However, all that never came to pass because I am married and have given birth to two children. Even right now, I think you can see that I am pregnant and in my own home. My husband has gone. To the ceter  but we always stay together.

Q8D. Description: It was in 2008 when I harvested enough onions. I have been a farmer since 1992 when I dropped out of school. I have never harvested that quantity - 4 bags of onion. I could dig, but always end up in a loss or harvest very little due to bad weather , bad/poor seeds. That year I bought modern seeds and tried to farm the modern way.But surely God was on my side because I just dug half an acre and harvested that much. I was able to pay school fees for children, open another project of bricklaying which I currently do as well as farming. I can be able to sell like 10,000 bricks each time I burn them. I cannot forget that moment.

You can sit home with my grandchildren, advise them and if there is any trouble/challenge it is just a matter of getting on your knees, pray and trust God in everything and things always happen positively. Could have gotten born again a long time ago, and maybe I shouldn't have lost my brothers and sisters to death due to drinking, witchcraft fighting and messing up with men/women or died of HIV/AIDS. If they knew JEsus they would have contributed themselves better. I thank  God I am still alive and born again.

Q8D. Description: Being voted a treasurer in a savings group in my community, I had never been a leader in my life. But to my surprise, in the year 2016 I was made one. I used to speak in public and I was always shy. My peers always to me as a coward. Even at home, my husband after drinking, he could taunt me by saying that I am like water in the pot, meaning very quiet. And that may be I am stupid. I used to feel bad, especially when I gave birth. I used to wonder how my children would feel hearing that about me. So one day there was a position of selecting treasurer in my group. I announced my interest and everyone laughed because they were very surprised. Anyway, we campaigned and I won the other two opponents. No ones ridicules me at all. I have gained. Respect in the Community and even my own husband respects me. The taunting ended. I walk around with a lot of dignity in our society and also because of that I want to cover for area councillor in the community.
description: Being voted a treasurer in a savings group in my community, I had never been a leader in my life. But to my surprise, in the year 2016 I was made one. I used to speak in public and I was always shy. My peers always to me as a coward. Even at home, my husband after drinking, he could taunt me by saying that I am like water in the pot, meaning very quiet. And that may be I am stupid. I used to feel bad, especially when I gave birth. I used to wonder how my children would feel hearing that about me. So one day there was a position of selecting treasurer in my group. I announced my interest and everyone laughed because they were very surprised. Anyway, we campaigned and I won the other two opponents. No ones ridicules me at all. I have gained. Respect in the Community and even my own husband respects me. The taunting ended. I walk around with a lot of dignity in our society and also because of that I want to cover for area councillor in the community.

Q8D. Description: 2020 I was a member of a farmer's SACCO, where we had a demonstration garden and we planted groundnut. We had invested our money out of the struggle and the headers of the SACCO after harvesting the groundnut, decided to sell without our notice and use the money alone. The SACCO collapsed, people lost their money, including me, and now people hate each other in our community.

Q8D. Description: In the year 2014, after my primary leaving examination and during that vacation, I just saw something like a swollen boil.It had a lot of pain. This was accompanied by loss of conscience and sometimes move anyhow, always to the direction of the road. My mother could just come for me, but I thought I wanted to be knock. Maybe I die. My friend took me to church and prayed and just after some time I became OK and now I'm still in school. Though the pastor had prophesied that I was bewitched and I had the spirit which was leading me to death.

Q8D. Description: I lost my father in 2003, so I was growing up with my mother alone. My mother was a housewife who did not have any job or any source of income. In 2021, I went to Kampala to work as a house girl in someone's home.The Lady of the House was very abusive and could not appreciate my work, so I escaped and moved away to Kireka where my sister was working, but she could not stay with me. However, she gave me transport t return to Tororo. When I came back, my brother took me.For a hairdressing course at someone salon in Atangi Trading Center. That was around October 2021. I managed to learn the skills of hairdressing. It is because of this course that I am able to maintain myself and also help my mother. People in my community appreciate my work and they respect me.

Q8D. Description: The moment I became an adult and married my wife in 1997, this made me to feel a real man because before I got married, I was all alone. Work and get some money but it all ended up in drinking. I didn't have plans. I was always going to night clubs and people used to call me useless boy, so my parent/father Advised me to get settled down by getting married. So I got married and now I am responsible man. I have my own Boda Boda bicycle do farming of sugar cane and also sit among adult even at the drinking joint. I and my wife do have five children and they were all in school, three and in primary and one daughter in secondary.I also do subsistence farming with my family, whereby sugar cane is for cash and subsistence farming of crops like maize, beans, cassava, Millet, etcetera are for food. I am a changed man.

Q8D. Description: In 2016 I got a loan from finance trust. Things were difficult for me. It was a loan of 800,000 SHS. I wanted to use the loan for beginning business. Instead I used the money on feeding and paying school fees. The bank people started to look for me because I had defaulted.One day they come. When I was in the house, my children told them that I was not at home, but they entered the House and pulled me out. I then managed to escape and run away. They could not follow me because they were smartly dressed and could not run through the Bush. However, in 2017.I called my brother-in-law who was working in Kampala, who helped me by paying 300,000 SH.Then by chance my step sister brought her husband for introduction. I was also able to get 400,000 SHS and some how I managed to clear the law.After clearing the loan I was very happy because I was at peace. I'm now a free man in the community.

Q8D. Description: I grew up in a very humble background. This made me drop out of school in P3. When my parents were told that someone is looking for a house girl, they sent me to that family in Kampala. When I was there, I learned all a lot of housework. This was in 2013. When I felt I was tired of living in someone's home, I returned back home. In 2014 I got married. The family that I got married in treat me well because I am hard working.I am also able to assist my parents in one way or another. The experience that I went through made me be what I am today.

Q8D. Description: I grew up in a very difficult situation. I lost my parents at a very tender age at one year and then my elder sister took me up. Got married at a teenage age I lived with my first husband for nine years. In that marriage, I got two children, a girl and a boy. Unfortunately, my husband died in a motor accident. I was forced to go back to our home because my husband's people forced me out. When my children grew to their youthful ages, I left them and decided to get married again. That is how I decided to get married to this Mukeso man in Kwapa. Currently in this home I have no children of my own, but the man I married has also two children. His wife divorced him and married somewhere else. These children respect me and love me. We used to sleep in a hot but ths son has built for us a permanent house. He also support us with household items. At church, the priest teaches the gospel that talks to my heart. This always comforts me that even if I worry of my earthly situations, I remember that God loves me.

Q8D. Description: I got married to my husband in 1962. I come from Padhola and my husband is an Itesot. Life was not very easy because my husband's people were under looking at me as someone from a poor family. And then I only gave birth to girls. They are seven in number. My husband loved me and was very supportive, but his family members tried to undertook me as someone who only produces girls.In 1982, one of my girls became mentally sick. She ran mad. It was quite very challenging. However, one of my brother-in-law and his wife were supportive and also my brother. They contributed money towards the treatment of my daughter.I also become close to the church. My church members prayed with us. The Rev also used to pay us visits. The teachings in church helped me to stand strong in the Lord. When my daughter become fine, she was able to go back to school and currently she is doing very well all my.Children are are currently doing well and I thank God for it, so people in my community respect me and some come to me for advise.

Q8D. Description: In 2009, I was involved in a very tragic accident. I had travelled to Soroti to take my A Jap forms to be filled by the local authorities. On my way back around Magodes, a trailer hit the taxi we were traveling in. I broke my arm. But there was a pastor from Malas Malaba called Father Lawrence. He took me to Tororo Hospital and called my parents, they come and took me to Mbale Hospital where I stayed for two weeks. My hand did not heal well, it shortened and that is why I am lame now. I gave up with education just like that. In 2015, I was invited for a training on reproductive health. That is when I met my husband. My husband and his family are very supportive to me. I feel loved and I am moving on.

People used to talk about my home negatively. However, today I have a cow that is giving me milk and I am able to sell some milk to other people.I like what it taught in church because the Lord of God comes to pass one time. A pastor told me that I would be a happy woman at one point, and indeed the prophecy has been fulfilled.

Q8D. Description: The baptism of my child, the first born child who is a girl. It was made a special day in that my husband made a simple party for us.This happened recently, actually last year in 2021 and the month of October 28th. Back then I was wondering on how I would go about it. However, my husband encouraged me to become down. But the problem is my husband does not want to dig does not do any work because he just makes up and goes were to the center in house around drink. I struggled to look for money for baptism by digging for other people for money. I managed to save enough and registered our child on church Asinge Catholic Church. Enough. My husband was present for the event. We made a simple party people turned up and I am much recognized as a good Christian. Recently they almost made me a quire leader, but still I am a quire member because my record with the church is very good. Society respects our family Because we are registered to as God fearing family.

Q8D. Description: It was my brother's wedding ceremony. I remember it happened on Friday 2013 March. We were all taken to church for the mass was held by the parish priest and thereafter the ceremony was brought back home. What occurred there was video coverage. They played music band all over the village. When reaching home, we get many visitors in the environment, meanwhile waiting for the bride and bridegroom to see physically. Thereafter, people ate food, drunk, cakes, danced the whole day that day. That makes me remember the party was so colorful and pleasant.

Q8D. Description: One day at the church, one member stood willingly to wed his wife Justine and Christiano last year, June 2021. The mass was led by the host parish priest of Kwapa Catholic Church. Thereafter they function was extended whole for after party in church. I returned personally so the event physically very interesting, enjoyable whereby many people attended in large number. I ate a lot of food, drinks when we were having hard. The invited people, started presenting their gifts to the bride and bridegroom. After the gifts presented, music interlude was there and it was enjoyable the whole day up to morning. The event was so colorful that made me to remember that wedding is a gift from God, so it's encouraged me a lot whereby I felt so happy.And enjoyable that event that I will never forget in my life as Richard personally.

Q8D. Description: I am an orphan and in 2019 my mother was not able to raise school fees for me. She asked me to remain home for at least two years to enable her to get some money for fees since she was paying fees not only for me but also for my other siblings one day.I went to a approach our father (Catholic priest) and explained to him what I was going through. After a serious interaction with him, he assured me that he would take care of all my school needs, which he has done. I am now a teacher by profession. I cannot forget that day because it marked the beginning of my future. I'm really very grateful to God for that day.

Then my husband had to marry a much older co wife who bore five kids for him. Since then I have never been happy, but living for God's purpose.

Q8D. Description: In 2006, when I was riding, I knocked a dog that was crossing the road. I fell off the motorcycle and broke my arm. I was hospitalized for two months. These event in my life made me a strong believer and made the group members strong. I feel sad though, because my left hand is several inches shorter than the right one.

I learned that any woman should get married in a home where she is accepted but not tolerated. What has kept us together amidst this fight is that I pray in the same faith with my husband and are of similar background.

Q3. What kind of people were you leading: I lead a choir that includes employees, employers, and people from different walks of life
Q8D. Description: In 2020, my neighbor was involved in an act of bestiality. Moreover, as a family man this incident disturbed the whole neighborhood including his family. Many condemned not only him but also the acts, because it was the first time we ever witnessed this.The worst of that he is Catholic, but my church and other born again tried to preach to him to change, but he has refused up to the day.However, we have never given up on him. Some people even claimed that this is a curse combined with the existence of a spiritual shrine in their home. We have learned that it is important to know where our children go for marriage before we consent to have them taken. Lastly, it is good to share a religion because that eases life and reconciliation in case of any challenge.

Q8D. Description: I have a child who had totally failed to talk. He had no speech but one time. This year, 2022, a voice told me to talk to a priest, father Okoth Paul. Every time I see this boy, I see a miracle child. Since then, my neighbors who used to talk ill about my Catholic faith reduced on the ill comments they used to make.

Many students have retarded their talents because of this disqualification. The problem is, managing students of different backgrounds is quite tough because everyone has their own character.The community has a challenge to collectively strengthen up their children to avoid having such stubborn character in school.

Q8D. Description: In 2019 we were having a youths friendly match (football), my church St. Mark against Saint Paul and I unintentionally broke a leg of a friend. Became so scared but later recollected myself, went and carried him off the pitch, took him back home (parent’s home), so we later resolved as youths of Saint Mark to contribute to his treatment which lasted close to two months. The church, especially youths, were sold.Courageously standing with the common cause of making our colleague recover and up to now we still hold those friendly matches. You would think that this could end such programs, but incidentally we continued to connect. This event united the youths of parish, no matter their faith I belonging.

Q8C. Other event: I got an accident- fell off from a tree
Q8D. Description: In 2016, I climbed a tree to cut branch for timber. Little did I know I know bees were up from now here the bugs stung me and I couldnt help but jump which ended badly. I got a terrible fracture on my lfet leg. Hospitals couldn't do much that time, so my dad opted for a traditional healer. Someone who fix bones locally. I cannot forget this accident because apart from being from poor background, the people we belong with in the same group were less concerned. I lost in many ways. I no longer play football. I can't run and no longer walk the way I used to walk. I learned that one should appreciate God for life everyday little Dino. I could be just like that. All my hobbies are just wasted.

Q3. What kind of people were you leading: Member of public men under police force and police in general
Q8D. Description: In 1979 (the fall of Idl Amin). At that time of Amin when I was in service my in Group attached Muslims in the community and the whole thing was nasty. The situation was terrible because.Tanzania troops penetrated the country to overthrow him and oblivious became so visible in the community I lived then. I can actually remember colleagues I was with. Of course, some already died, but I will forever live to tell this because I witnessed with my eyes. People lost lives in such a terrible way and today I learned that it is so difficult to live with people whose values are totally divergent and different from your own. There is a level whose compromise may not achieve anything at all. Being a Catholic, I witnessed bad blood between.My in Group at the Muslims that time. But then I realized personal values are more important than community values.

Q8D. Description: I was studying smoothly and doing well at school. But in 2015 I developed a sickness that affected my left leg. It swell and my parents moved with me in several hospitals and native doctors but I wasn’t getting any better. Towards the end of 2015, I was taken to Nagongera Deliverance Church under Pastor Odongo where they prayed for me and I got healed. This was a turning point for me because I started to move well and the swelling disappeared. The Church continued to support me and my family.

Q8D. Description: When I was growing up, things were difficult because I was an orphan. In 2007, my sister took me to stay with her at her home. She registered me with an organization under comparison. This organization took over the responsibility of paying my school fees. I was able to go through my ‘O’ level without difficulty. I am now doing a course in business administration. Because of this myself esteem has improved and I'm living a happy life with my community members.

Q8D. Description: I used to be a drought. Every money that I would get be used for buying alcohol. I was hostile and used to fight. But in 2019 I recollected myself and made a decision to stop drinking. My wife also cancelled me a lot.Today I am very changed person. The money I get I use it for developing my home. There is peace at home and even in the community. My family is happy because I am able to provide them with the basic requirements. I am also a good example to the men in my community.

Q8D. Description: When I got married to my husband's, things were difficult.I had no money of my own to carry out with my personal activities. In 2013, I collected some money from digging in people's gardens. I used the money to begin business of sailing fish. This business was greatly helped me. I am able to pay my children's school fees, dress up and improve my household. The community members have no reason to move long distance looking for fish because they easily come to buy for me at home.

Q8D. Description: They got married as a second wife and the home I got married in has little land, so there was a challenge of where to cultivate. However, in 1986 my brother-in-law who was a clerk at the Sub county gave me land to hire (sub-county land). This enabled me to cultivate variety of food stuff through digging. I was able to educate my children until they qualified and now they are working and they are supportive to us as a family and also the community. I was also able to produce enough food to cater for us at home and even give out to those who do not have.

Q8D. Description: In 2015, I gave birth to a lame child. This child was always sick to an extent that we were taken to Mbale. They did not have money, but by God's grace, the church where I pray from came in to support me.Then one day, in the very church I pray from (grace of heart), they told us that some whites are going to support children from poor families. One of my boys was suggested. The white man who supports him sent him gifts and money. I got money and bought goats. When the goats increased in number, I changed them with the cow. Currently we have two cows. I am happy that at least now we have something at home. If it wasn't for the white man I would not be like this now.

Q8D. Description: Church event: Welcoming the Bishop of the church. One day last year, 2021, I had a first Holy Communion event at church whereby one of my children was confirmed had complete the training session. We starting by having a mass, held by the bishop and many reverend in church. Thereafter, many of the Christians went back home, meanwhile celebrating dancing and me myself, I was very happy, joyful because my children had confirmed as a truly Christians and has accepted the Lord as a personal savior in life. Before reaching home, we branched the trading center called Rubongi Center where we had drivers and it was my first time because I had money that day. After the after party held at the center, we went back home for food where we ate a lot. Lastly, we see God has done the best in my family and I will never forget in my life.

Thereafter, many of the Christians went back home, meanwhile celebrating dancing and me myself, I was very happy, joyful because my children had confirmed as a truly Christians and has accepted the Lord as a personal savior in life. Before reaching home, we branched the trading center called Rubongi Center where we had drivers and it was my first time because I had money that day. After the after party held at the center, we went back home for food where we ate a lot. Lastly, we see God has done the best in my family and I will never forget in my life.

Q8D. Description: Ever since I lost my husband died in late 1990s, up to now I'm left a widow whereby managed to help upbring my children until they grow up knowing they never had a godparent. And it was challenging for me to educate the children, but God willingly I was helped and managed to educate six children in number and they have completed their education all. Therefore, what makes me happy? All my children are working and they are going to support a lot, both financially and spiritually.The loss of my husband has made not to forget that educating children is so hard. As I'm a widow, I will never forget in life aspect as a generally hard stressing factor in life, but generally I'm now used as a God loving person in life.

Q8D. Description: The birth of my first born child in the year 1979 in the month of December I was just 18 years, but I.Push. Normally people kept telling me that I am young and may end up tesarion section, but that never happened. I pushed a fat bouncing baby girl. We make a simple party, but that gave me a lot of respect. That is the best experience I got in my life because the fear of. Loving a Pagan child just never happened. Though we separated with my husband, but I lived to enjoy that joy.
