Q8D. Description: The day of my wedding in 1999, November 1st. It was on a normal day of Thursday in August 1999 when my husband.The father of our five children suggested that he wants to wed me in the church in Aechilleti. At first I thought it was a joke because my husband was a womanizer and I had lost my faith in him.He could change women oftenly. At that time he had three children. I was only enduring to stay in that marriage because of the children that we had together.In one time separated actually it was two times in my marriage life was really crumbling. I was worried to catch HIV AIDS at any time but had nothing to do anyway since I have to endure for the sake of my children, I was also praying for a happy marriage in future. But little did I know that God was answering my prayer sooner than I thought. The announcement to legalize our marriage went on for three months. And guess what? No one came in to stop until on that day, that special day of November 1, 1999, we took our vows of wedding. Ever since he wedded me, he stopped womanizing.I don't have HIV and above.Our love grow more each day. I am now 49 years in Mary.Which and we are both old, aging together. My husband is 64 years old, I am 63 years happily married. And I am a leader of the BCL in our church, because I am wedded and happily married and a regional treasurer at the church.

Q8D. Description: The fact that I went to school even if I reached in only primary six class has helped me so much. Well, before when I was a child, I used to hear people really ridicule my parents because they have never gone to school at all.Others could even utter funny statements like “if you want to see a problem or even make people laugh, ask Adong Juliet’s parents to write their names. You will see stars as they will become a blind.” Such statement could really hurt me. So I struggled and reached at least be six. I could not complete because my parents died when I was very young, mother died when I was 8 years old and father died when I was 10 years old. However in my life. Marriage, life. I have not lived here. Write my own name, speak English. I can even be elected in positions like chairperson women group because I can read and write and I am educating my children. When they come home from school I can check their books and help them to write some letters. I have seven children in total. I am 37 years and my husband is 40 years.

Q8D. Description: The day my boyfriend/fiance proposed to marry me in the year 2018 in the month of June. Member by then I was in primary six class. I used to stay hungry at school. Even in our home one could hardly find what to eat because we used to survive by going to dig for other people who pay and then get money to buy books, even food at home. Both of my parents are alive, but life was very hard. I could never run away from home because I had no one to turn to. So when I clocked 15 years after seeing my periods for two years because I started menstruation at 12 years, all I wanted was to get someone who can marry me so that some of my troubles can reduce. The good note that chance came to me in 2008. My husband is 23 years old and we have stayed in our marriage together since then. I at least have my own home, and I am independent with two biological children. As we age of 20 years I have never lacked what to eat. We struggle, but at least we always got food and have our good village structure.

Q1. Describe Leadership Roles: Head girl at school in priamry
Q8D. Description: The power of prayer whereby I got my leg healed miraculously. It was in the year 2013 when I started feeling sick on my leg. No one knew where the sickness came from, but all I know is that every in June my leg would swell infecting me with a lot of pain on my whole body. I could even fail to walk for about 3 months each time it starts paining.That went on for over three years and I was even named as a girl with seasonal sickness. I really got tired of living and at one point I even just wished to die. However, in 2017 February they prayed for me and I got miraculously healed and never, ever feel any pain at all. And it is like I have never suffered from that sickness. I can walk very well and even run. I got pregnant and live even given birth to two children with no sickness at all, that is the most significant event in my life.

Q1. Describe Leadership Roles: Women leader at parish level/Female representative councillor
Q8D. Description: Winning the elections in 2020, my campaigns were really challenging. I was so much cared and almost gave up, but I saw immense help from the people. My friends and strangers all campaigned for me. I was in the NRM party and you know it was not easy because most people were falling or showing high interest in the people power, many people sacrificed other properties, money to give those who demanded for them so that they can vote for me. When I saw that I gained courage and the power to speak, I even never knew I would talk that much but I made, got a campaigning manager and guess what in May 2021 I won the elections. I'm very famous and must even, added a position women counselor of the parish level. Now a voice to the voiceless.People, women and all other vulnerable groups in my parish and some county at large. I am a leader of that time t is on need.

Q8D. Description: The day my daughter got married, she introduced her husband and all the dowry was being paid. Her name is Alwani Agnes, who got married in Sagere village in 2008. I have 5 girls and one boy. Before my daughter got married, people used to taunt me saying there is nothing good that would come out of my home and especially my children. Community members used to overlook us because offer all my children had bad luck dropped out of school and the other two daughters. That older one left from P7 and the other in P5 glass because we did not have no money to keep them in school anyway. I had almost accepted my faith is bad and maybe I won't ever feel the happiness of my children. However, all that changed in 2008. All those stocks ended. My family is not respected and Can you imagine my children?Are called blessed because even my daughter now stays in Kampala with her husband in the capital city. Also freely and with wheel attended people's functions without any fear and people want to be my friend, I have so many connections because now people I advise other fellow women and people's daughters not only in my community and also villages, I have a miracle.

Q8D. Description: Not falling sick for a very long time. Currently as we speak it is around 23 years.I was lost sick in the year 1999. I felt sick, suffered from malaria. Yes, I am poor, but sickness has not been a portion of my life. I am now 55 years, but all I remember is that I have been falling sick twice the whole of my life. Mother, who is late right now, always told that I was very sick leave and I was still a child. However, when I made 12 years old at age, she said everything changed about me.She said she could take me to the hospital almost weekly and I looked malnourished. No one ever thought that I would end up being this healthy. I have always been healthy, much as I only give birth to one child who pushed on and I think my wound closed. I have never had any birth.To another child again.I am a healing and strong woman. No sicknesses that disturb people here and there.

Q8D. Description: The day I got married in 1984/4/8 was the greatest day of my life and to top it up when he my husband took dowry or paid dowry to my parents. It is something I least expected. But he did it. Before that. People, including my fellow women, were just undermining me, saying I only got married for food. I am not a real woman. I had no respect of all. But now, after the dowry was paid, I gained respect. I have always moved.With a lot of going because I know for sure I am in my own home. I am also a reference example, especially in my father's clan. They really strengthened my marriage. Actually I also I am on the Committee of the Women that councils women, even in my own village where I came from in Namwanga village found in siwi sub county. Couldn't achieve that if I had not been officially married with a final seal of the wedding, I am wedded with my husband.

Q8D. Description: It was back in 2012 and I had a heart problem which almost took my life.So there was a day dedicated for praying for the sick. I personally went as and told God today is the day I would get my miracle. Indeed, ever since after that prayer, I have not got any complications with my heart. Other Christians who attended the prayer also got their miracles. This has really made me and the rest of the church members that there is no burden that God cannot offload. It has not only strengthened my faith but also for other within our community, especially those who knew what I was going through.

The rest of the community members who were not baptized the younger age were able to learn from me and also got baptized at the mature age. I can't forget this day because I will make me inherit the Kingdom of God which I thought I would not get.

Q8D. Description: Back then, in the year 1985, my husband abandoned in the home, this home of ours and joined the Army and was working in Kilauea.I was eight months pregnant. I really suffered because I was having a three extra children to take care of. One month after I gave birth, I really suffered to care for all three children, school fees including so I begin digging for people so as to get what to eat. I didn't even have clothes to wear, and for my children it was.With that, went on for about 10 years. Later on, my husband returned. He had a lot of weight. He was very fat. And me, I was so miserable, including the children. He returned at night. I'm home. Someone came to pick him, noting that they had forgotten a bag of money at the police station. I cried. Life was so hard, so hard and us. And at the moment when I had seen hope again, it disappeared. Anyway, later on he sent someone to give us some help, but it was so little, so I went to Nagongera cried for a pastor and he put for us some small structure a grass thatched house. However.They have eventually collapsed as thieves knocked it down. So I ended up going back to Nagongera and stayed with Pastor. He rented for us a room there. Shortly I heard news that my husband had died. And guess what he ciscumed to HIV/AIDS on 29/12/1992. I honestly mourned, but truly in my heart I was thankful to the Lord. This is because that night when he returned, if he spent a night at home, I am sure I would have had intercourse with him and I would also be infected. Maybe I would be as well be dead by now.And our children would be total orphans. Ever knowing well that I was almost used to suffering, I continued to struggle educating our children.And also Pastor helped with some money since I was a cook in his school at Nagamura to start following up for my husband's money with military offices. I left there my forms and come back home. After three days I got a call saying they have put their money in the account and that was about five years after his death.I was able to put up this structure, this beautiful house and also complete the children's fees payment.They all managed to enroll for colleges. I didn't even have clothes to wear, and for my children it was.With that, went on for about 10 years. Later on, my husband returned. He had a lot of weight. He was very fat. And me, I was so miserable, including the children. He returned at night. I'm home. Someone came to pick him, noting that they had forgotten a bag of money at the police station. I cried. Life was so hard, so hard and us. And at the moment when I had seen hope again, it disappeared. Anyway, later on he sent someone to give us some help, but it was so little, so I went to Nagongera cried for a pastor and he put for us some small structure a grass thatched house. However.They have eventually collapsed as thieves knocked it down. So I ended up going back to Nagongera and stayed with Pastor. He rented for us a room there. Shortly I heard news that my husband had died. And guess what he ciscumed to HIV/AIDS on 29/12/1992. I honestly mourned, but truly in my heart I was thankful to the Lord. Maybe I would be as well be dead by now.And our children would be total orphans.
